eeded for normal test runs.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Python Binding Tests (`demo` test target)\n\n`test/CMakeLists.txt` line 85 sets an additional variable for the `demo` test (only when Boost.Python is enabled):\n\n- `PYTHONPATH=.` — makes the build directory's ledger Python module importable.\n\n`PyUnitTests.py` (actually a shell script template, not yet expanded) references `PYTHONPATH`, `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`, and `DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH` pointing into the build's `.libs/` directory — these are populated by the `acprep`/autoconf build system, not CMake.\n\n---\n\n### 6. `.test` File Variable Substitutions\n\nNo `.test` file uses shell environment variables at runtime (the grep for `$[A-Z_]+` excluding `$FILE` returned no matches). The only substitution tokens are:\n\n- `$FILE` — replaced by `RegressTests.py` with the absolute path to the test file itself (not an env var).\n- `$sourcepath` — replaced by `RegressTests.py` with the harness source path (also not an env var).\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nTo run the test suite correctly, you need:\n\n1. **`TZ=America/Chicago`** — mandatory; forced by every test layer.\n2. **`PATH`** — must include the system tools needed by shell-piped test commands.\n3. **`HOME`** — should point somewhere without a `~/.ledgerrc` to avoid polluting test results (the `CheckEnvVars` tests force it to `/nonexistent`; other tests inherit the caller's value).\n4. **`LANG` / `LC_ALL` / `LC_CTYPE`** — locale vars, passed through; their absence or presence can affect string formatting in output.\n5. Platform-specific: `TMPDIR`/`TEMP`/`TMP`, `SYSTEMROOT`/`COMSPEC` (Windows), `MSYSTEM`/`MINGW_PREFIX` (MSYS2).\n\nNo `LEDGER_*` variables should be set in the calling environment when running the standard test suite — the harness strips them all to ensure test isolation.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>46809</total_tokens><tool_uses>22</tool_uses><duration_ms>107279</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-